Salute is a song by British girl group Little Mix for their Salute Little Mix album second studio album of the same name 2013. It was released on 30 May 2014 as the album's third single. It was co-written by the group Perrie Edwards, Jesy Nelson, Leigh-Anne Pinnock and Jade Thirlwall with TMS production team TMS Thomas Barnes, Peter Kelleher and Ben Kohn and Maegan Cottone, and produced by TMS. Lyrically, Salute is a girl-power song, being called a call to arms for women everywhere to stand up and fight whatever imaginary enemy is standing in their way, with military metaphors, war sirens, and hip-hop and trap music genre trap influences, drawing comparisons to Destiny's Child and Beyonc's Run the World Girls. 

Music critics gave the song positive reviews, with most praising its empowering lyrics and military-inspired drum beats. Some even noticed it would fit perfectly as an opening song for the tour, as well as being one of the strongest tracks of 2013. The song became a top-ten hit on the charts of Scotland and United Kingdom, becoming the band's sixth top-ten single in the UK, while reaching the top-twenty in Ireland and top-forty in Belgium. A music video for the song features the band dancing in an underground warehouse with an entourage of male dancers, some of whom are on leads. To promote the song, the band performed in many TV shows, including Britain's Got Talent and the Today U.S. TV program Today Show.

 Background and release 
After winning the The X Factor UK series 8 eighth series of The X Factor UK The X Factor UK, British girl-group Little Mix released their debut album, DNA Little Mix album DNA, in November 2012. The album received generally favorable reviews from music critics,cite web url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/dna/little-mix  title= DNA- Little Mix  work=Metacritic  publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. date= 19 November 2012  accessdate= 15 December 2012 while also being a success on the charts,http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/bpi-sales-certification-to-be-automated/055448 BPI sales certification to be automated   Music Weekcite web url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1565729/little-mix-breaks-spice-girls-chart-record title=Little Mix Breaks Spice Girls' Chart Record work=Billboard magazine Billboard accessdate=5 June 2013 besides spawning the number-one single Wings Little Mix song Wings, as well as the top-three hit DNA Little Mix song DNA and the top-twenty singles Change Your Life Little Mix song Change Your Life and How Ya Doin'?.cite web title=Little Mix &#124; Artist &#124; Official Charts url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/little%20mix/ website=The Official Charts Company accessdate=8 July 2014 A few months later, the group stated that they were working on a new album, stating:  I think we probably might mature slightly for this album, but we want to keep the kind of uplifting message we had on the last one. ... Were just gonna make it better; step it up.cite news last1=Vena first1=Jocelyn title=Little Mixs Next Album Gives Them Goose Bumps url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1710312/little-mix-dna-sophomore-album/ accessdate=8 July 2014 work=MTV News date=10 July 2013 It's definitely matured more and it's a bit more R&B, they completed in another interview.cite news last1=Copsey first1=Robert title=Little Mix talk new album: 'It's mature, more R&B' url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a506070/little-mix-talk-new-album-its-mature-more-rb.html#~oJoSRAjT8E0fAq work=Digital Spy publisher=Hearst Magazines UK date=12 August 2013 accessdate=8 July 2014 The girl group recorded material in Los Angeles with producers Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis,cite news last1=Corner first1=Lewis title=Little Mix working with Janet Jackson producers for new album - video url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a510552/little-mix-working-with-janet-jackson-producers-for-new-album-video.html#~oJoSQC0BOdZpC8 accessdate=8 July 2014 work=Digital Spy date=28 August 2013 as well as TMS production team TMS, who produced their number-one single Wings. The production team produced six tracks on the album, including Salute, which also became the album's title.cite web title=Little Mix  Salute CD at Discogs url=http://www.discogs.com/Little-Mix-Salute/release/5101657 website=Discogs accessdate=8 July 2014 On 5 April 2014, the group announced the track as the album's third single. They teased their single announcement with a video of them rehearsing a dance routine to the track alongside their backing dancers.cite news last1=Rigby first1=Sam title=Little Mix announce new single 'Salute' - listen url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a562669/little-mix-announce-new-single-salute-listen.html#~oJpnODrfzljirJ accessdate=8 July 2014 work=Digital Spy date=5 April 2014 Later, on 19 April 2014, the group revealed the single's cover art.cite news last1=Rigby first1=Sam title=Little Mix unveil new single 'Salute' artwork url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a565636/little-mix-unveil-new-single-salute-artwork.html accessdate=8 July 2014 work=Digital Spy date=19 April 2014

 Composition and lyrics 
File:Beyonc Knowles GMA Run the World cropped.jpg thumb 150px The song received comparisons to the work of Beyonc and her former group Destiny's Childcite news title=Little Mix - Salute - MusicOMH url=http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/little-mix-salute accessdate=24 July 2014 work=musicOMH date=11 November 2013
Salute was written by band members Little Mix Perrie Edwards, Jesy Nelson, Leigh-Anne Pinnock and Jade Thirlwall, with TMS production team Thomas Barnes, Peter Kelleher, Ben Kohn and Maegan Cottone, while production was done by TMS production team TMS. Cottone recorded their vocals, while also providing vocal arrangement, while Barnes was also responsible for drum instrument drums, Kelleher provided Keyboard instrument keyboards and Kohn also contribute with bass instrument bass. It was recorded at Starlight Sound.cite AV media notes  title=Salute  others=Little Mix  date=2013  type=liner notes  publisher=Syco Music, Sony Music Entertainment Sony Music  Salute features war sirens, stinging guitars and military chants,cite web url=http://uk.omg.yahoo.com/news/little-mix-cement-premier-girlband-status-salute-182700655.html title=Little Mix cement premier girlband status on 'Salute'  publisher=Yahoo! last=OBrien first=Jon date=2013-11-06 accessdate=2013-11-08 featuring hip-hop beats and a trap music genre trap experimentation. It starts with an air raid siren  a warning and call to action - building to a frantic and frenetic climax, as noted by Jamie Clarke of So So Gay.cite web url=http://www.sosogay.co.uk/2013/album-review-little-mix-salute/ title=Album Review: Little Mix - Salute publisher=So So Gay last=Clarke first=Jamie date=2013-11-14 accessdate=2013-11-14 Rachel McGrath of Entertainment Wise wrote that the song draws comparisons to Beyonc and Destiny's Child, claiming that it has Run The World Girls-esque chant and strong beat. Harriet Gibsone of The Guardian also saw similarities, calling it a Beyonc boot-camp stomp.cite news url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/nov/07/little-mix-salute-review title=Little Mix: Salute  review publisher=The Guardian last=Gibsone first=Harriet date=2013-11-07 accessdate=2013-11-08 Phil Mongredien of The Observer wrote that the song turns into 'Invincible Five album Battlestar' by 90s boyband Five band Five as it reaches its chorus.cite news url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/nov/10/little-mix-salute-review title=Little Mix: Salute  review publisher=The Observer last=Mongredien first=Phil date=2013-11-10 accessdate=2013-11-10

Lyrically, Salute brims with girl-power motifs dressed up in military metaphors, affirming that being a woman is about more than just looking good: You think we're just pretty things/You couldn't be more wrong/We're standing strong, carry on, they sing.cite web title=Little Mix - Salute - Plugged In url=http://www.pluggedin.com/music/albums/2014/little-mix-salute.aspx website=Plugged In accessdate=24 July 2014 Mongredien called it a call to arms for the world's women. As noted by Nick Barnes of Unreality TV, the girls try and recruit all the women out there to salute and join their army. Janelle Tucknott of Renowned for Sound went on to explain that the song is all about women empowerment and joining together to fight a war, assumedly that of bullying and negativity and the struggle for equal rights.cite news last1=Tucknott first1=Janelle title=Single Review: Little Mix  Salute url=http://renownedforsound.com/index.php/single-review-little-mix-salute/ accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Renowned for Sound date=23 May 2014 You think were just pretty things. You couldnt be more wrong, the girls sing, sending a message not only to any sexist standing out there but also to every woman who just needs a little motivation to believe in themselves, Kadeen Griffiths of Bustle noted. Were standing strong. We carry on cant stop a hurricane. Ladies, its time to awake!.

 Critical reception 
Jon O'Brien wrote for Yahoo! that the song is a perfect attitude-laden statement of intent. Lewis Corner of Digital Spy noted that the Blitzkrieg siren and fierce attitude on female empowerment call-out 'Salute' is primed for an arena tour intro,cite web url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a529598/little-mix-salute-album-review-a-razor-sharp-record-that-makes-a-mark.html title=Little Mix Salute album review: A razor-sharp record that makes a mark work=Digital Spy publisher=Hearst Magazines Hearst Magazines UK last=Corner first=Lewis date=2013-11-08 accessdate=2013-11-11 while McGrath of Entertainment Wise called it one of the strongest openers of 2013.cite news url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/reviews/132189/ALBUM-REVIEW-Little-Mix-Salute title=ALBUM REVIEW: Little Mix - Salute last=McGrath first=Rachel date=11 November 2013 publisher=EntertainmentWise accessdate=24 December 2013 Mongredien of The Observer thought that it shouldn't work, but is delivered with such chutzpah that it has a certain ludicrous charm, while Clarke of So So Gay named it a perfect, in-your-face opening track. Nick Barnes of Unreality TV was very positive, writing that the song has everything youd want in a track, noting that Salute would serve as an amazing opening to the girls tour to get the audience really pumped and it would, strangely, work as a single as its very infectious.cite web url=http://unrealitytv.com/review-little-mix-salute-accomplished-rb-record-showing-bags-progression/ title=REVIEW: Little Mix  Salute: An accomplished R&B record showing off bags of progression publisher=Unreality TV last=Barnes first=Nick date=2013-11-10 accessdate=2013-11-10

Commercial performance
Salute debuted at number 74 on the UK Singles Chart week of 11 May 2014,cite web title=UK Singles Top 75: Compiled By: The Official UK Charts Company url=http://acharts.us/uk_singles_top_75/2014/20 website=Official Charts Company accessdate=24 July 2014 becoming the greatest gainer the following week, climbing to number 51.cite web title=UK Singles Top 75 - Compiled By: Official Charts Company Issue Date: Sunday May 18, 2014 url=http://acharts.us/uk_singles_top_75/2014/21 website=Official Charts Company accessdate=24 July 2014 It cracked the top-forty in its third week, climbing to number 35.cite web title=2014 Top 40 Official Singles Chart - UK Archive: 31st May 2014 url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2014-05-31/ website=The Official Charts Company accessdate=24 July 2014 After falling to number 40, the song climbed once again to number 24.cite web title=2014 Top 40 Official Singles Chart - UK Archive: 14th June 2014 url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2014-06-14/ website=The Official Charts Company accessdate=24 July 2014 The song peaked at number 6 the following week, on 21 June 2014,cite web title=2014 Top 40 Official Singles Chart UK Archive 21st June 2014 url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2014-06-21/ website=The Official Charts Company accessdate=24 July 2014 becoming the band's sixth top-ten single.

Music video
The music video for the song was directed by Colin Tilley. It premiered on YouTube on 2 May 2014 cite web url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kjpa0SMOug0 title=Salute on YouTube publisher=YouTube and has over 24 million views as of September 2014. It features the band dancing in an underground warehouse with an entourage of male dancers, some of whom are on leads.cite news last1=Davidson first1=Amy title=Little Mix reveal video for new single 'Salute' - watch url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a568286/little-mix-reveal-video-for-new-single-salute-watch.html#~oKU2oGxnrBfAWZ accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Digital Spy date=2 May 2014 As noted by Kadeen Grifiths of Bustle, band members Nelson and Edwards even march with the men on leashes at one paint. And yet they are next to her rather than behind her or beneath her, dancing with her rather than against her or in front of her, as if the girls wanted to be clear that men and woman are equal, but its the women who are in control right now.cite news last1=Griffiths first1=Kadeen title=LITTLE MIX'S SALUTE IS A FEMINIST ANTHEM BEYONCE WOULD BE PROUD OF  VIDEO url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/23136-little-mixs-salute-is-a-feminist-anthem-beyonce-would-be-proud-of-video accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Bustle date=2 May 2014

Live performances
Little Mix performed Salute live for the first time on Britain's Got Talent series 8 Britain's Got Talent.cite news title=Little Mix Raunchy Salute Performance on Britain's Got Talent with Diversity url=https://screen.yahoo.com/little-mix-raunchy-salute-performance-195614803.html accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Yahoo! They also performed on the Today U.S. TV program Today Show on 18 June 2014.cite news title=WATCH: Little Mix Performs on Today Show url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2014/06/little-mix-today-show-perrie-edwards-performance-video/ accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Heavy The band also performed the track during the Summertime Ball 2014.cite news title=Little Mix - 'Salute' Live At The Summertime Ball 2014 url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/little-mix/performances/salute-summertime-ball-2014/ accessdate=24 July 2014 work=Capital radio network Capital FM date=21 June 2014 It also became the opening track for their The Salute Tour Salute Tour.

